Property.Value: CREATE PROC LAST_LOGIN @ID INT,@LASTLOGIN DATETIME AS

Property.Name: BodyScript
Property.Value: BEGIN SELECT C.Id, C.[Name], C.ShortName, C.CreatedDate, U.Username "Created By", C.UpdatedDate, U2.Username "Updated By", C.[Address], C.[Status] FROM Company "C" LEFT JOIN Users "U" ON C.CreatedBy = U.Id LEFT JOIN Users "U2" ON C.UpdatedBy = U2.Id WHERE C.[Status]=1 END

Property.Value: CREATE PROC [dbo].[SELECT_COMPANIES] AS

Property.Name: BodyScript
Property.Value: BEGIN SELECT U1.Id, U1.FirstName, U1.LastName, U1.Username, U1.[Password], U1.ContactNo, U1.Email, U1.Gender, U1.City, U1.CreatedDate, U3.Username "Created By", U1.UpdatedDate, U2.Username "Updated By", U1.[Role], U1.[Status], U1.LastLogIn FROM Users AS "U1" JOIN Users "U2" ON U1.UpdatedBy = U2.Id JOIN Users "U3" ON U1.CreatedBy = U3.Id WHERE U1.[Status]=1 END

Property.Value: CREATE PROC [dbo].[SELECT_USERS] AS

Property.Name: BodyScript
Property.Value: BEGIN UPDATE Users SET FirstName=@FNAME, LastName=@LNAME, [Username]=@UNAME, [Password]=@PASSWORD, ContactNo=@PHONENO, Email=@EMAIL, Gender=@GENDER, City=@CITY, UpdatedDate=@UPDATEDDATE, UpdatedBy=@UPDATEDBY, [Role]=@ROLE WHERE Id=@ID; END
